The paper deals with link scheduling algorithms for maximizing throughput in multicast wireless networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and architectures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of physical interference models and optimization techniques, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of power control, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY).
